SIMPLE: bounden
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bounden
<hw>Bound"en</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>p. p & a.</pos> <ety>[Old. p. p.
of <ets>bind</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Bound; fastened by bonds.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 171 --></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Under obligation; bound by some favor rendered;
obliged; beholden.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This holy word, that teacheth us truly our <qex>bounden</qex> duty
toward our Lord God in every point.</q> <rj><qau>Ridley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Made obligatory; imposed as a duty;
binding.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I am much <qex>bounden</qex> to your majesty.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bounder</ent>⟦br⟧
